external_knowledge:
- "shining stars" metaphorically refers to highly-rated productions;
- "accolades" represent the awards the productions have received;
- "glowing reviews" and "average ratings" refer to the ratings given by users;
- "stand out as the brightest" indicates sorting in descending order and selecting the top 5 results;
- 'Production Co. A' is the specific production company being queried.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT name) AS total_unique_names, TOTAL_CHANGES() AS total_changes
FROM crews
WHERE name <> 'Laurits Flensted-Jensen';

SELECT SUM(views)
FROM analytics
WHERE production_id = (SELECT production_id FROM productions WHERE title = 'Baraki');

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name
FROM users u
INNER JOIN user_ratings ur ON u.user_id = ur.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'cinematic masterpieces' refers to movies; 'decade that gave us smartphones and smart TVs' refers to the years between 2010 and 2020;
- 'spirited engagement of at least one hundred critics' means at least 100 user ratings or reviews;
- 'abundance of reviews' metaphorically describes the count of reviews or ratings a movie has received;
- 'fervent is this engagement' indicates the number of reviews, suggesting how actively the movie was engaged with.

sql:
SELECT company_name 
FROM production_companies 
WHERE company_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "turn of the millennium to recent years" refers to productions released between 2000 and 2020;
- "performance and popularity" indicates the inclusion of financial success (revenue) and critical reception (IMDb rating);
- "movie types" is synonymous with "genres" of productions;
- "number of films in each category" refers to the count of productions within each genre.

sql:
SELECT name, role
FROM crews
WHERE name = 'Laurits Flensted-Jensen';

SELECT AVG(imdb_rating) AS average_imdb_rating
FROM productions
WHERE type = 'documentary' AND year = '2020';
